<p>The UK government has accepted a report which recommends that bone scans should be available for women at high risk of osteoporosis. However, parliamentary health secretary Baroness Cumberlege rules out a comprehensive screening programme, saying she "does not ... want the NHS to offer screening to all women over 50 years old. In the light of existing knowledge about the disease, this would be quite wrong." She says that the NHS should decide at local level what priority to give to bone scans.</p>
